                            "children": [
                                {
                                    "name": "SCENES_README.md",
                                    "type": "file",
                                    "content": "# Scenes Folder\n\nThis folder contains all Unity scenes used in the project.\n\n- **Menus**: UI-related scenes (MainMenu, Loading, Pause).\n- **Levels**: Main gameplay stages, divided into Campaign and Bonus.\n- **Sandboxes**: Technical test scenes for mechanics and lighting.\n- **Cutscenes**: Narrative-driven non-interactive cinematic scenes.\n\n## Naming Convention\n- Levels: `Level_01`, `Level_02`, etc.\n- Campaign: `Campaign_X`.\n- Bonus: `Bonus_X`.\n- Sandboxes: `Sandbox_Test_X`.\n- Cutscenes: `Cutscene_X`.\n"
                                },
                                {
                                    "name": "SCENES_GUIDELINES.md",
                                    "type": "file",
                                    "content": "## Guidelines for Scenes\n\n1. Keep scene names short and descriptive.\n2. Use prefixes for clarity (e.g., `Menu_Main`, `Level_01`).\n3. Document any special lighting or mechanics in the scene.\n4. Sandbox scenes should not be included in builds.\n5. Cutscenes must be optimized for performance and memory usage."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
